"{\"uid\": \"eater.com-24208969-paris-2024-olympic-village-dining-hall-food-reviews-tiktok\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"So far, the chocolate muffin is the dining hall's standout dish  If you buy something from a link, Vox Media may earn a commission.See our ethics statement.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 99, \"end\": 108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vox_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3512740808220185e-31, \"text\": \"Vox Media\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vox_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vox_Media\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If TikTok has changed anything about the Olympics, it's that Olympics viewers around the world now have access to unfiltered, behind-the-scenes looks into what life is like in the Olympic Village (this year, that includes the offshoot Olympic Villageon a cruise ship in Tahiti).\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 161, \"end\": 167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.583727098029696e-41, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}, {\"begin\": 338, \"end\": 353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9813263357682727e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 428, \"end\": 434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999995220605, \"rank\": 4.73403149679461e-10, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We know how Olympic athletes sleep (oncardboard bedswithScrub Daddy-esquemattresses).\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We know how they get changed (quickly, and withmakeshift coveringssince not all the rooms have curtains).\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We have learned that Olympic Village Tinder is,apparently, disappointing.\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And thanks to all theseOlympic Village vlogs, we also know more than ever aboutwhat the food is likeinside the dining hall.\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics organizers promised \\\"healthy, gourmet and creative food, with more plant-based and local options,\\\" but dining in the Olympic Village has not gotten off to the smoothest start: Followingreports of an egg shortagelast week and complaints about not having enough meat, Olympics organizersannounced todaythat they'd fixed their early logistical problems and added \\\"700 kilos of eggs and a ton of meat\\\" to the menu to better meet the athletes' needs.\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 954, \"end\": 969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9813263357682727e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On TikTok, though, the situation does not look too different from your standard large American college dining hall.\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1286, \"end\": 1292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.583727098029696e-41, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}, {\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9913961727162726, \"rank\": 0.008678461732016864, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one video, Tina Rahimi, a boxer who's representing Australia, walks viewers through the dining hall to show the halal section.\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1414, \"end\": 1418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Turner\", \"score\": 0.9990906516952668, \"rank\": 0.0005746054072022974, \"text\": \"Tina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Turner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Turner\"}, {\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999997826457966, \"rank\": 2.1374688655331863e-07, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We see that the dining hall is arranged by cuisine (World, Asian, French, and halal), with salad bars available outside each section.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1589, \"end\": 1594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_cuisine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.840218496862794e-27, \"text\": \"Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_cuisine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_cuisine\"}, {\"begin\": 1596, \"end\": 1602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999343037369267, \"rank\": 6.51059348294454e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There appears to be a huge variety of food, with stations for pastas, grilled items, sides, and beverages.\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other videosshowa large hand-washing station before entering the dining hall, an abundance of fresh fruit, and - lest you think it's all boring - plenty of baked goods, crepes, and cookies.\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a staggering amount of food when you consider how long the Olympics goes on: During the two 15-day periods of the Olympic and Paralympic Games, the organizersexpect to serve13 million meals.\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 2157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(And that does not include the foods different delegationshave shipped to Paris for their athletes.)\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2232, \"end\": 2237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.258843218016569e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But how does it all taste?\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The seeming verdict: The food is good, not great.\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2336, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In her video, Rahimi offers just an unenthusiastic nod after tasting her meal.\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's good.\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2427, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not really... seasoned,\\\" says Aleah Finnegan, a gymnast from Missouri who's representing the Philippines,in another video.\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2463, \"end\": 2477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleah_Finnegan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aleah Finnegan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleah_Finnegan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleah_Finnegan\"}, {\"begin\": 2494, \"end\": 2502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Missouri\", \"score\": 0.4853914432783413, \"rank\": 0.7421253963393165, \"text\": \"Missouri\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Missouri\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Missouri\"}, {\"begin\": 2526, \"end\": 2537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.495888987834932e-14, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though there is a seasoning station, she notes, the influx of athletes to Olympic Village has made the cafeteria more crowded and makes the process of getting food take longer.\", \"from\": 2556, \"to\": 2732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2630, \"end\": 2645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9813263357682727e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee Kiefer and Gerek Meinhardt, thefencing couplewho are representing the US, have revieweda few of their meals.\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2734, \"end\": 2744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Kiefer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lee Kiefer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Kiefer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lee_Kiefer\"}, {\"begin\": 2749, \"end\": 2764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerek_Meinhardt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gerek Meinhardt\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerek_Meinhardt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerek_Meinhardt\"}, {\"begin\": 2808, \"end\": 2810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9966462072631048, \"rank\": 0.0033492237830630564, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their reviews would suggest that Sodexo, who's handling the dining halls, is doing okay with the meat mains, like chicken tikka and curry beef, but not so well with the carb sides, like couscous and sticky rice.\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 3058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2880, \"end\": 2886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sodexo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If any dish has been the standout of the Olympic Village dining hall,it's the chocolate muffin, which has appeared in multiple videos from different athletes.\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3101, \"end\": 3116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9813263357682727e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its biggest fan, however, is the Norwegian swimmer Henrik Christiansen, whohas made four videosabout the chocolate muffin alone.\", \"from\": 3219, \"to\": 3347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3252, \"end\": 3261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.6523935945729386, \"rank\": 0.4891942949741431, \"text\": \"Norwegian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 3270, \"end\": 3289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henrik_Christiansen_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.6621615443867334, \"rank\": 0.5102040816327192, \"text\": \"Henrik Christiansen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henrik_Christiansen_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henrik_Christiansen_(swimmer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But really, it's the social dynamics at play that seem the most reminiscent of college dining, with every delegation clustered into its own little clique.\", \"from\": 3349, \"to\": 3503, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Freya Colbert, a swimmer representing Great Britain, jokingly sether videoof the dining hall to an audio track that says: \\\"It's hell in there; it's horror.\\\"\", \"from\": 3504, \"to\": 3660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3504, \"end\": 3509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freyja\", \"score\": 0.9816828889462116, \"rank\": 0.018621013065577143, \"text\": \"Freya\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freyja\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freyja\"}, {\"begin\": 3510, \"end\": 3517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Colbert\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.265019049965522e-13, \"text\": \"Colbert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Colbert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Colbert\"}, {\"begin\": 3542, \"end\": 3555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999791439682966, \"rank\": 2.084597892781404e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And just as that setting always highlighted the stratification of social groups, the Canadian rugby player Piper Loganshared a videoabout the imposter syndrome feeling of being in the dining hall while Serena Williams walks by.\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3746, \"end\": 3754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_Canada\", \"score\": 0.6001447362712876, \"rank\": 0.6652322883935291, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 3863, \"end\": 3878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The freshest news from the food world every day  The freshest news from the food world every day  This is the title for the native ad  The rise of the \\\"butter chicken experience\\\" and other similarly exclusive offerings proves it's no longer enough to simply offer a straightforward dish  After the Cronut, the cruffin, and every other sweet version, savory croissants are finally the center of croissant innovation  A new wave of Filipino coffee shops is playing with flavors like jasmine and jackfruit and highlighting under-sung coffee beans  Pastel blob art, begone - make way for lived-in furniture and Grandma's tchotchkes  It's not just fast food: Even trendy restaurant owners are accepting the fact that \\\"everyone loves chicken\\\"  In this excerpt from her new book, food writer Ruby Tandoh unpacks why every recipe now looks and sounds the same  This is the title for the native ad  \\u00a92025Vox Media, LLC.\", \"from\": 3890, \"to\": 4800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4188, \"end\": 4194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronut\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cronut\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronut\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cronut\"}, {\"begin\": 4320, \"end\": 4328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipino_cuisine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.114875033143862e-20, \"text\": \"Filipino\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipino_cuisine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipino_cuisine\"}, {\"begin\": 4435, \"end\": 4441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pastel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.811265860842622e-26, \"text\": \"Pastel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pastel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pastel\"}, {\"begin\": 4796, \"end\": 4799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999948633048968, \"rank\": 5.136721372746001e-06, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved\", \"from\": 4801, \"to\": 4820, \"entities\": []}]}"